Home › News › STÉPHANE RAMBAUD-MEASSON BECOMES GROUP EXECUTIVE VICE PRESIDENT AND MEMBER OF THE MANAGEMENT BOARD OF FAIVELEY TRANSPORT 




News

26/02/2014
STÉPHANE RAMBAUD-MEASSON BECOMES GROUP EXECUTIVE VICE PRESIDENT AND MEMBER OF THE MANAGEMENT BOARD OF FAIVELEY TRANSPORT
Faiveley Transport is pleased to announce that, as of March 17th 2014, Mr. Stéphane Rambaud-Measson will join Faiveley Transport as Group Executive Vice President.
 
 Mr. Rambaud-Measson will be a member of the Group Management Board and will report to Mr.Thierry Barel, Chairman of the Management Board. He will have full delegation of power over the entire Sales and Marketing, Projects, Engineering, and Operations of all operational sites globally. Mr. Thierry Barel will retain the chairmanship of the Executive Committee. The Finance, Human Resources and Corporate Development Directors will continue to report to him, while Executive Activity Directors and the Sales & Marketing Director will now report to Mr. Rambaud-Measson. In joining Faiveley Transport, Mr. Rambaud-Measson brings with him a wealth of experience of the railway industry, and an outstanding track record he gained as President of Bombardier Transport Passengers Division and most recently of CEO of Veolia Verkehr, the leading train and bus private operator in Germany. His contribution will help Faiveley Transport accelerate the growth and performance of the company. He will play a significant part in achieving our ambitious goal of becoming a leader in serving train builders and operators globally with high added value integrated Systems and Services.












