Stéphane Rambaud-Measson | about.meStéphane Rambaud-MeassonStéphane Rambaud-Measson was appointed President, Passengers, Bombardier Transportation in July 2008, and held this position until November 2011, covering all passenger trains businesses, from Light Rail Vehicles up to very high speed, for Europe, Asia and Australia. In this position, he increased the Division turnover by 70%, and reinforced Bombardier position as market leader by winning several large scale projects such as commuter and regional trains in France, a new regional train platform in Germany, large Very High Speed contracts in China and in Italy and the largest metro project in India.Stéphane Rambaud-Measson was appointed President, Passengers, Bombardier Transportation in July 2008, and held this position until November 2011, covering all passenger trains businesses, from Light Rail Vehicles up to very high speed, for Europe, Asia and Australia. In this position, he increased the Division turnover by 70%, and reinforced Bombardier position as market leader by winning several large scale projects such as commuter and regional trains in France, a new regional train platform in Germany, large Very High Speed contracts in China and in Italy and the largest metro project in India.


